To give knowledge for reading, translating and form analysis of the Greek New Testament. Chapters 1-14 from the textbook "New Testament Greek for Beginners" by Jaan Unt are studied, texts from the Gospel of Mark or the first epistle of John are read, translated and analysed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To get an overview of the structure, morphology and vocabulary of the New Testament Greek and acquire skills for reading, translating and grammatical analysis of New Testament texts.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A Student - gets to know the grammatical structure and morphology of the New Testament Greek;  - recognizes the case and number of nouns, adjectives, pronouns and participles, as well as the forms of the verbs in the present, imperfect, aorist, perfect, pluperfect and future tenses in active, medial and passive voice, the principles of using pronouns should be familiar;  - is familiar with the vocabulary of the New Testament;  - is able to make use of the Greek language dictionaries;  - is able to translate New Testament texts with the help of a dictionary.
